# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example — TEMPLATE ONLY. Copy this file to ".env" and paste real keys in.
# The real ".env" is git-ignored and must NEVER be committed. This template
# contains placeholders only — no real keys live here.
#
# Why THREE Groq keys (one provider, split by phase)?  See INSTRUCTIONS.md §7.
# Splitting the work across three keys keeps each key's free-tier rate limit for
# its own job so nothing throttles mid-demo.
#   GROQ1 → Extraction: column identification     (llama-3.3-70b-versatile, text)
#   GROQ2 → Extraction: blurry-image OCR fallback (llama-4-scout-17b, vision)
#   GROQ3 → Analysis + reporting phase            (NOT used by extraction)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GROQ1=gsk_your_extraction_column_id_key_here
GROQ2=gsk_your_vision_ocr_fallback_key_here
GROQ3=gsk_your_analysis_phase_key_here

# Path to the Tesseract OCR binary (OPTIONAL).
# settings.py auto-detects Tesseract on the PATH and in the standard install
# folders, so most machines need nothing here. Uncomment and set ONLY if your
# Tesseract lives somewhere non-standard. A path that doesn't exist is ignored.
#   macOS (Homebrew): /opt/homebrew/bin/tesseract
#   Linux:            /usr/bin/tesseract
#   Windows:          C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\tesseract.exe
# TESSERACT_CMD=C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\tesseract.exe
